description: Meet David Boring: a nineteen-year-old security guard with a tortured inner life and an obsessive nature. When he meets the girl of his dreams, things begin to go awry: what seems too good to be true apparently is. And what seems truest in Boring's life is that, given the right set of circumstances (in this case, an orgiastic cascade of vengeance, humiliation and murder) the primal nature of humankind will come inexorably to the fore.
name: David Boring

description:
Collects stories featuring Dan Pussey, from the pages of Eightball.

Step with me now, backward in time to the early 1990s, when the 'comic book', previously disdained by all but the cretinous few, found itself swept from the backwash along a tidal wave of cultural upheaval to the very forefront of all human endeavor!

Here before you sits the principle protagonist of this bold movement, an ink-stained dreamer who would, in his time, provide a hungry America (and parts of Canada) with the cultural sustenance (a toothsome admixture of heroic fantasy and grim realism) it so richly merits! Ladies and Gentlemen, I give you, Dan Pussey!
name: Pussey!: The Complete Saga of Young Dan Pussey

description: Rick Grime's horrific adventure continues. Everything he knew is gone, and the search for his family begins. Rick sets out for Atlanta, the last known location of his wife and son.

name: The Secret of the Dragon's Den

description:
The latest offering from the red-hot Marvel Knights line reunites the seminal creative team of Garth Ennis and Steve Dillon for a sequel to their legendary story arc, “Welcome Back, Frank.” It all starts when two mobsters take a trip to the zoo and piss off the wrong monkey. Limbs are lost (the kind you can’t easily replace), vultures are fed (with said appendages), and then things get, like, really crazy. Like back-from-the-dead crazy. That’s right -- she’s back and she wants payback. Ma Gnucci. Eighty-five pounds of hairless, armless, legless evil. Collecting PUNISHER: WAR ZONE #1-6.

Hardcover Edition
name: HC/TPB

The Rock Troll called Ulik has clashed with Thor - but he still doesn't scare the Punisher! Don't miss a knockdown scrap! Also starring Daredevil, the Black Widow, Shang-Chi and Dagger!

By Chuck Dixon and Ed Barreto.

Plus: Planet Hulk continues! The Hulk leads his warriors into battle - and Caiera the Oldstrong witnesses the insane Red King on a killing spree! Will anyone survive the war for Sakaar?

By Greg Pak and Aaron Lopresti.

Also: Squirrel Girl meets Speedball! Will romance bloom? Tippey-Toe knows, but she ain't tellin'!

By Fabian Nicieza and Paco Medina.
